  m_Name: Mushroom_13_Coppercup
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Hollowfen.Data.MushroomFieldGuideData
  _id: coppercup
  _commonName: Coppercup
  _latinName: Aleuria aurantia
  _edibility: 0
  _edibilityLabel: "Edible \u2014 delicate"
  _description: "A brilliant orange cup fungus known outside the village as orange
    peel fungus. It has no stem, no cap, and no gills \u2014 just a thin, open cup
    that looks like someone dropped citrus peel on the path. It is the kind of find
    that makes Wren stop walking mid-step."
  _idFeatures:
  - Small cup-shaped fruiting body
  - Copper to burnt-orange inner surface
  - Thin pale outer edge
  - Often fruits in loose arcs along forest edges
  _habitat: Bare soil, path edges, disturbed ground, and leaf litter where woods
    meet meadow
  _season: Late summer through autumn, especially after rain
  _lookalikes: Other orange and red cup fungi. Avoid cups growing from dung or rotten
    debris, and do not trust color as the whole identification.
  _notes: Pretty enough for market baskets, fragile enough to punish careless handling.
    It is a visual reward for players who scan the ground carefully.
